Finally, the clouds part. A heavenly ray of sunlight shines
down upon the world as the \C[14]Exalted Four descend from
the firmament.
Exalted Four
\{\C[11]This is the beginning of a new era.\.
\C[9]An era of healing.\. \C[14]An era of flourishing.
Exalted Four
\{\C[10]Together, we will build a new world.
A world of forever peace. Walk with me.
endcut/Pro3
The Exalted Four \C[14]preside over the reconstruction of the
world.\C[0] The true damage is incalculable, but their \C[3]gentle,
benevolent guidance\C[0] helps humanity regain some of what it lost.
It is not the old world that humanity rebuilds. It is a new
world; a world of compassion, hope and, for many, \C[3]redemption.
If you did Dan quest.
It's difficult for him, but Dan \C[3]moves on from streaming.\C[0] He
leaves games behind and, for the first time in his life, starts
putting others first. He remains close to \N[1], and they
\C[10]game together every weekend.
Dan is devastated when he loses his streaming channel for
directly filming the visitor. It's not long before he \C[3]starts
up a new channel\C[0] and he's back to his usual antics.
If you didn't do Dan quest.
Life without his family is difficult for Joel to adjust to.
He continues to live with \N[1], and in time, comes to view
him as his \C[3]new family.\C[0] He never outgrows his curiosity and
innocence.
\N[1] raises \N[8] not as a pet, but \C[3]as a child.\C[0]
Their relationship has its ups and downs, but in the end,
\N[8] always loves \N[1] as a father.
Ernest decides that his rambling days are over and \C[3]settles
down for good.\C[0] He and Squeakums entertain children with their
music, which people continue to play long after he's gone.
If you reunited with mother.
Sophie returns to her mother, although she regularly comes to
visit \C[14](and make mischief).\C[0] Eventually, she \c[3]sets off on her
own\C[0] in search of adventure. She always sends \N[1] cards
of her travels.
If you didn't reunite with mother.
Sophie never does find her mother. For a time, she stays with
\N[1], but eventually \C[3]sets off on in search of her family.\C[0]
She always sends \N[1] letters about her travels.
Did Leigh Quest - Chose Beast and Leigh
Leigh \C[3]reconnects with her family,\C[0] who accept the new side of
her - and recognize that part of it had always been there. She
eventually gives up her rivalry with \N[1], and they always
remain close friends.
Did Leigh Quest - Chose Beast
Leaving behind the old Leigh forever, the Beast sets off to
grow even stronger. In time, she \C[3]founds a place for likeminded
people\C[0] who find it hard to adapt to the New World of peace.
Did not do Leigh Quest
It's difficult for Leigh to adapt to the New World, and she
frequently finds herself in trouble. She becomes a \C[3]wanderer,\C[0]
forever in search of someone stronger.
Did Hellen Quest
With goodbyes reserved only for \N[1], Hellen leaves the
city and wanders, never staying in one place for too long.
Wherever she goes, a \C[3]garden blooms\C[0] not long after.
Did not do Hellen Quest
Hellen disappears without a word, never to be seen again. It's
not long before a strange but beautiful ivy \C[3]begins growing
on the apartment,\C[0] eventually engulfing it.
It takes a long time for Xaria to \C[14]learn to become comfortable
with herself.\C[0] She realizes the burden her behavior placed on
the people around her, and apologizes to the people she hurt.
\C[3]Especially \N[1].
Not everyone agrees with the Exalted Four's dominion over the
New World. Xaria and Monty \C[3]join a resistance group\C[0] and struggle
to find a new path for humanity.
Audrey easily settles into the role of surrogate mom, \C[3]taking
care of countless children\C[0] orphaned by the Visitor's ordeal.
She becomes a beloved figure and learns to thrive in spite
of her strange, new biology.
It's not enough to collect, Morton learns. Sharing is the true
joy of collecting. \C[3]Morton opens up a small shop,\C[0] sharing his
various knick-knacks and doo-dads with people. He always keeps
the best stuff, though.
Now part of the Exalted Four, Aster diligently leads humanity's
rebuilding as its \C[3]omniscient and benevolent ruler.\c[0] Almost every
moment of his life is occupied with work, but he \C[14]always makes
time for \N[1].
For the first time in a very long time, \C[3]Papineau rests.\C[0] There
will be enough work to last lifetimes. Surrounded by friends,
he allows himself a moment of tranquility before
reconstruction begins.
Phillippe finds it difficult to adjust to life without a spore
princess. For the first time, \C[3]he is truly on his own.\C[0] The spore-
moth begrudgingly accepts \N[1]'s help in establishing
himself, and eventually\C[14] buries the hatchet with him.

The Roaches \C[14]spread\..\..\..\. \C[0]and \C[5]spread\..\..\..\. \C[0]and \C[10]spread\..\C[0] Eventually,
intelligent roaches colonize the entire planet, forcing
humanity to accept that it may have a (very silly) competitor.
Roach quest - democracy
The political divide between democratic and royalist roaches
deepens every year. The Roach New World Order flounders in
its infancy, and nearly 70% of post-Visitor social
media activity is cockroaches engaging in heated debate.
Roach quest - democracy
Nevertheless, roaches continue to vote for \N[1] as
Prime Minister of the Roaches - even when it's not an election
year.
Roach quest - monarchy
Nevertheless, roaches continue to cherish \N[1] as
King of the Roaches. They even make him a little throne.

\N[1]'s life \C[14]never goes back to the way it was.\C[0] Surrounded
